Taiwan Stocks: Powerchip Tech, Realtek Semiconductor, TSMC

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-05T05:42:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/realtek-semiconductor-tsmc-yulon-motor-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 205.49 points, or 2.7 percent, to
7,551.57, the biggest loss since Aug. 19.  Chipmakers:  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT) slumped by the
exchange-imposed daily limit of 6.8 percent to NT$4.25 and
 Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT) fell by the same amount to
to NT$2.19. The two companies were made “full-delivery stock”
by the Taiwan Stock Exchange and Gretai Securities Market,
barring trading of the shares using short-selling or margin
trading. The companies were downgraded because their book values
per share have fallen below the regulatory requirement of NT$5,
according to statements by the Taiwan bourses.  Realtek Semiconductor Corp. (2379)  (2379 TT) dropped 1.1 percent
to NT$45.95. The chip designer said August sales fell 9.1
percent to NT$1.66 billion ($57.2 million) from a year earlier,
according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT) retreated
1.3 percent to NT$66.60.  Morris Chang , chairman and chief
executive officer of the world’s largest contract chipmaker,
said his customers’ confidence in the global economy has
weakened. Slowing global growth will impact the chip market,
Chang said in Taipei.  To contact the reporter on this story:
